  "description": "**Residential Heating in Austria: National Trends and Regional Diversity**\nIn the broader context of Austria’s energy balance, thermal energy is a heavyweight: more than half of the country's final energy consumption is dedicated to heat production. A significant portion of this energy fuels the heating systems of Austria’s roughly four million primary residences.\n**The National Heating Mix**\nWhile the transition to renewables is underway, fossil fuels still maintain a significant footprint. As of the current reporting period, the national breakdown of heating systems across all primary residences is as follows:\nThis information has been published initially on https://www.energie.gv.at\n",
